The architecture uses a deliberate separation of concerns. The early notebooks establish environment state, validate raw inputs, and enforce explicit schemas. The middle notebooks generate durable Delta tables for cleaned order history and dimensional analysis. The later notebooks create higher-level analytics outputs and validations that can be consumed both by humans and by the dashboard. This progression is important because it keeps the report tables downstream of stable warehouse contracts rather than ad hoc notebook cells.

