The clustering stage produced three segments that are easy to interpret. Cluster 0 behaved like frequent loyal shoppers with average total orders of 33.28 and reorder rate of 0.6521. Cluster 1 behaved like light occasional shoppers with average total orders of 7.54 and basket size of 6.63. Cluster 2 behaved like large-basket stock-up shoppers with average basket size of 17.12. The report intentionally highlights the segment interpretation and the \(k\)-selection evidence together because clustering results are much more convincing when the choice of \(k\) is explicit.

